Title: Secrets of the Swamp
Description: Collect Ancient Stone Tablets and Rubbings from any Ancient Plaques within Sunken Aspect, and return them to Legatus Fulvius in the Reekwater Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: A question I ask myself every day, but of course, the answer is that it's my duty, as a citizen of New Corsica and of Aeternum.\n\nI believe there are secrets stirring in the primordial waters of this land.
InProgressResponse: I've only just learned of these tablets, but I have high hopes.\n\nBring back the tablets or charcoal rubbings from the plaques and I'll share whatever I can translate.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Aha! Did I mention I'm a scholar of the Ancients' language? I've spent centuries studying - let's see what I can decipher here...\n\nHm. Yes, as elsewhere, it's clear they forced humans into servitude - the Guardians.

Title: Hope Springs Eternal
Description: Investigate the Ancient ruins of Skyview Repose, and return to Legatus Fulvius in the Reekwater Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I absolutely agree. There's only one additional clue I can decipher from the writings you procured.\n\nIt seems the humans made some sort of pilgrimage to a primordial spring in the northwest mountains.
InProgressResponse: Healing waters in the mountains… why would the Ancients sends their servants there?\n\nPerhaps they were benevolent overlords? Hurry now, this could help us learn more!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Aha, you've returned! Unlike Abbington... at any rate, let's see what you found.\n\nHm. It appears the site was dedicated to a ritual of creation, involving... yes, some kind of devices.

Title: Paths Unseen
Description: Colllect any remnants of the Ancients you can find in Rackham's Hollow. Then report to Legatus Fulvius in the Reekwater Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Well, the map you recovered seems to locate the source of the devices used in the rituals.\n\nIt appears to be an underground facility hidden in the caves the locals call Rackham's Hollow. That, is where we search next.
InProgressResponse: Be wary in the caves. I've heard the Lost have domain there.\n\nBut if it gives us clues about the Ancients' technologies, it's worth any risk.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Thank the gods you've returned! I was beginning to worry! And what are these...? \n\nOh... the Guardian Hearts we've seen in other places? This suggests the ritual at the spring was... perhaps where these were... Implanted?

Title: Anatomy of the Heart
Description: Search for any remaining Ancient artifacts within the ruins of Sha Makogai. Then report to Legatus Fulvius in the Reekwater Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: The ruins of Sha Makogai - they appear to have been the seat of the Ancients' power in this region.\n\nIf you're willing, and very careful… any artifacts remaining there may tell us more. Mars protect you, my friend.
InProgressResponse: The ruins of Sha Makogai have been explored before, but perhaps something remains there of interest.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You have proven quite capable, my friend, and helpful too. Let me see what you've recovered.\n\nIndeed, a functioning Guardian Heart... and opened? What's this inside? An azoth crystal, and... vines? From a Dryad, no less.

Title: Seek and Hide
Description: Uncover the whereabouts of Antiquarian Abbingdon, last sent to Syleio Seko.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: It means we need to find Abbington - he knows more than I do about this business.\n\nHe was last out at the ruins of Syleio Seko - please, you must go find him… or his notes, if that's all that remains.
InProgressResponse: Please, make haste. If Abbingdon has not returned by now, it could be bad.\n\nWe need him, or his work, at least.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Stellar timing! I knew Fulvius would eventually send someone.\n\nBut I couldn't leave behind this artifact I've discovered… of course, I can't seem to collect it, either.

Title: Secrets Best Left Unshared
Description: Distract the Starvault Guardians while Antiquarian Abbingdon frees the Ancient artifact.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Because THIS is what he's after - an artifact the Ancients used to extract souls and turn them into azoth!\n\nPower beyond comprehension! I need to get it out of here… it belongs in a museum!
InProgressResponse: Distract the Starvault Guardians downstairs, and I'll pry the relic loose. \n\nWe can do this - we have to.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: What news, my friend? I feel we are close to finding the secrets of the Ancients here.\n\nTell me, did you find Abbingdon? What happened to the old fool?

Title: An Expanding Threat
Description: Investigate the Lost Pirates at Maria's Rest. Then report to Headmen Onizuka in the Reekwater Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: The Lost, the empty vessels… the Siren Queen. I told them, but others here are only concerned with the Angry Earth.\n\nNow it's Corruption everyone fears, but soon, the Siren Queen will come for us all.
InProgressResponse: Go on now, go to Maria's Rest and see for yourself.\n\nDefeat as many pirates as you can, but it will not be enough.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: [BLANK]

Title: Defiance and Doubt
Description: Track down the Pirate deserter, possibly hiding out in Shipflight Comb in Reekwater.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: This final note mentions a town to the northwest. From Maria's Rest, that would be Shipflight Comb. I would start there.\nBe careful… the spirits of that place rest uneasy, and may not take kindly to your intrusion.
InProgressResponse: Shipflight Comb was once a bustling town, full of energy and life. What changed there, no one knows.\nNo one, except the spirits that remain.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Don't kill me, please! Mercy! I'm not… not with them. Not anymore! Not for a long time really…\n\nI didn't know! She was once not so bad, a good leader, brave, inspiring even…

Title: A Hunger for Freedom
Description: Find, craft, or purchase Meager Meals and Fresh Water for Katring Sanders in Reekwater.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Oh, because she's gonna take the whole island. I mean, she's... wait - you're working me!\n\nLook, I'll tell you things, but only if you get me food and water first. I've starved to death many times hiding here. It hurts!
InProgressResponse: I'll tell you what the Siren Queen's all about, but you gotta get me some grub first. \n\nBerries, hardtack, an old shoe - I'll eat anything at this point.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Oh, sweet mother ocean... praise you! This'll keep me fed for... I don't know how long.\n\nAlright then, I guess one good turn deserves another and all that bilge... I'll tell you about the Siren Queen.

Title: Queen's Gambit
Description: Destroy the mysterious Cursed Banners throughout Reekwater, then return to Katring Sanders.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Harnessing the island's magic, I figure. She's made these strange... 'banners' outta flotsam and relics.\n\nIt's like they suck the life out of you and give it to her. Ever since she put 'em up, she gets stronger.
InProgressResponse: Good luck tearing down those banners. \n\nI mean it may be the only hope, but don't ask me to do it.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Well now, look who's played the odds and lived to tell! \n\nYou're pretty mean scallywag, aren't you? Not as mean as the Queen, mind you, but you got salt.

Title: Shivering Timbers
Description: Put a stop to the salvage operations at Scavenger's Shore and Bleachwood Coast, and report back to Headman Onizuka in the Reekwater Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: That's when I hid, but they started getting salvage for those banners from all the wrecks on the shoreline.\n\nIf you really want to gum up her plan, you should strike those salvage operations. Don't come back here, though.
InProgressResponse: I think I'll be staying here. Like I said, it's safer.\n\nI mean you got salt, but if I was a betting woman -  and I am - I'd bet on the Siren Queen. No offense!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: At long last, you return! I was beginning to think you might've joined the Siren Queen's crew!\n\nNow you have seen it with your own eyes, haven't you? She's as much a threat as this Corruption, I tell you.

Title: Words of Power
Description: Search Syleio Seko for clues about the Siren Queen's plans. Then report to Headman Onizuka in the Reekwater Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Yes, and we must find out what that is. You have learned of this Ancient 'machine' she took from the ruins, yes?\n\nThat antiquarian - Abbington - he said her crew has been scavenging more such relics as well.
InProgressResponse: We must know what the Siren Queen ultimately seeks to accomplish before we attempt to confront her.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Bless the winds that brought you back. Let me see, what clues did you find at the Lighthouse?\n\nHm. These notes suggest her 'machine' has the power to steal souls from the living and channel them into another vessel…

Title: A Plan's Deconstruction
Description: Destroy the twisted Ancient relics in Mistywater Thorp. Then report to Headman Onizuka in the Reekwater Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Before now, I would not have thought so, but it does confirm my suspicions.\n\nThe Siren Queen has the potential to become an even greater theat than the Corruption.
InProgressResponse: I believe the Siren Queen's crew is using the relics to create more of these banners they put up across the territory.\n\nYou must put a stop to this.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You have done well. There are already reports that there are fewer of those cursed banners.\n\nLet us hope that this will arrest or at least very much slow down the Siren Queen's efforts. This settlement may well be spared.

Title: The Queen is Dead (Elite)
Description: Hunt down the Siren Queen's lieutenants, destroy the Ancient Machine, and defeat the Siren Queen. Then report to Headman Onizuka in the Reekwater Settlement.
PlayerPrompt: "Let's not keep her Highness waiting, then."
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Ha! Well said, {playerName}!\n\nNow, the Siren Queen’s lieutenants have spread throughout that hodgepodge 'fortress' to the south, one of whom holds the key to her sanctum... but we've been unable to discover which one.
InProgressResponse: After you light off that gunpowder, the Siren Queen won’t be pleased at all. You and your allies will need to be ready for the fierce battle ahead of you. I’ve heard the Siren Queen has control over storms. Be careful.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: We saw the plume of smoke from here, and heard the lightning strikes of the Siren Queen's fury! Since you made it back... can I assume she has been dealt with?

Title: Long Live the Queen (Elite)
Description: Hunt down the Siren Queen's lieutenants, acquire a key, and defeat the Siren Queen. \n\n(This Quest can be shared and repeated)
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Sadly, no. Elsewhere on Aeternum, could take a week to come back... around here, it's always faster. Must be something in the water.\nAnyway. Are you and your friends ready to tangle with her again?
InProgressResponse: Go on, off with you. You’ve things to do, I’ve things to do, and standing around won’t make any of them happen faster. Besides, you’ve kicked the Siren Queen back out to sea in the past, I expect you to succeed again!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: @0510_0101_longlivethequeen_complete_available_response

Title: On Floral Fauna
Description: Retrieve the Dryad journals dropped by Herbalist Langlais in the Glimmerfen. Then return it to her in the Reekwater Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: These lands are sacred to nature, and any affront to nature on Aeternum will cause a reaction here.\n\nThe relentless spread of Corruption has imbued the Dryads with unnatural strength, strength that threatens the balance.
InProgressResponse: My journals contain decades of insights regarding Reekwater and the Angry Earth.\n\nThey must be reclaimed or all my work will have been in vain.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Oh praise the Earth mother you've returned! These journals are everything to me.\n\nI hope my work might help us placate the Angry Earth in this turmoil and someday bring us back into harmony with one another.

Title: Pruning and Irrigation
Description: Provide Marsh Walker Afolabi with her requested fresh Dryad Cuttings from the Glimmerfen, and Azoth Water from Azoth Springs.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Because she has much to learn, and her growth can only be accelerate by adversity… but you have done no harm.\n\nPerhaps there is another way we might hasten her enlightenment?
InProgressResponse: The fresh Dryad samples and azoth water will give us greater insights.\n\nTrust the process, young one.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Thank you, child. Some might shy away from the Dryads when they seethe as they do. You are brave.\n\nAnd indeed these samples prove that the Dryads in Glimmerfen come from all over the island.

Title: New Growth
Description: Search the Virid Grotto for azoth crystals, and bring pieces of them back for Marsh Walker Afolabi in the Reekwater Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I am, but first, I ask your assistance in addressing a concern of my own. \n\nWhile Madilon has walked these waters for decades, I have done so for centuries, but I have never seen pure azoth crystals here... until now.
InProgressResponse: The Dryads in the grotto are enraged to a degree unlike any time I've seen in the past.\n\nDo take care collecting the crystals.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Your return warms my blood, young one. Let me see these crystals.\n\nAzoth indeed, and most peculiar to be growing there. I will have to study them, but I think I promised you something in return… what was it?

Title: Excising the Blighted Root
Description: Hunt down The Blight Bringer and any Blight Nodules in Lambent Muskeg, then travel to Fisher's Glory to ensure the Blight has not spread. Then report to Herbalist Langlais in the Reekwater Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: The greatest factor in the destabilization of nature now is of course the Blight.\n\nI suspect you have seen it elsewhere, but the threat is greater here, because the gathering of Dryads could cause it to spread.. well, everywhere.
InProgressResponse: Blight cannot be allowed to take hold here in Reekwater. The stakes are too high.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Good to see you back in one piece. Let us hope that your actions today helped curb the Blight.\n\nIt is a great relief to learn it hasn't spread to Fisher's Glory.

Title: Burden of Atonement
Description: Take the Dryad Offering to the Mysterious Altar in Fisher's Glory as an apology. Then report to Herbalist Langlais in the Reekwater Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: It is not difficult. Place this offering on the altar at the foot of Fisher's Glory, so they all can see it.\n\nJust... be on guard. One of the large dryads might come to forcibly extract your amends.
InProgressResponse: I appreciate you humoring me with this penance.\n\nMarsh Walker Afolabi would say we're wasting our time, but time will tell.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Ah, I can sense some measure of serenity returning to the marshes.\n\nYou have done the right thing, regardless of what anyone else says.

Title: Upstream Investigation
Description: Search Sha Makogai and the fallen lighthouse, Hingatirn, for any clues on the Dryads' presence in Reekwater. Then report to Herbalist Langlais in the Reekwater Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: For the water, you say? She really believes it's to bathe themselves in the azoth-infused waters here?\n\nI simply cannot imagine their motive to be so self-centered, so... self-indulgent.
InProgressResponse: I'm convinced that the Ancient ruins will give us insights.\n\nIf you don't find anything at first, just… keep trying.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: So you found something then? Let's see... oh dear, this is quite dreadful!\n\nThe Ancients dissected the Dryads for some nefarious purpose... I wonder if that's related to them coming here. Perhaps some cycle of vengeance?

Title: The Eternal Pool (Elite)
Description: Investigate the Eternal Pool and face whatever challenges lie within. Then report to Herbalist Langlais in the Reekwater Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Absolutely. It appears to be on the northern plateau, and that is indeed a place the Dryads protect quite fiercely.\n\nI'm sure it's where we'll learn the truth about them. Go if you dare, but I suggest you don't go alone.
InProgressResponse: There could be anything waiting for you up on the plateau. Best gather some friends and watch yourself.\n\nAnd make sure you take notes, and collect anything you can find! I want to hear about everything you see there!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You... returned. I can't even imagine what you must've witnessed there. The pool is pure azoth, isn't it?\n\nYes, I've spent more time studying the sketches you recovered. The pool is reason the Dryads come to Reekwater.

Title: The Dryad Promenade (Elite)
Description: Follow the Dryad Promenade path into the depths of the Eternal Pool, and lay the Protector of the Source to rest.\n\n(This Quest can be shared and repeated)
ObjectiveProposalResponse: The Protector of the Source exceeds his mandate - the pool belongs to all life forms.\n\nLike other Dryads, he too must return his essence to the waters. Do what must be done, young one.
InProgressResponse: To defeat the Protector of the Source, I would suggest you bring allies.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: [BLANK]

Title: The Original Guardian (Expedition)
Description: Collect the Guardian's Eye from Chardis in the Lazarus Well Expedition. Then report to Legatus Fulvius in the Reekwater Settlement.
ObjectiveProposalResponse: I'm not entirely sure, but some of the glyphs show images of a massive, many-eyed Ancient Guardian.\n\nSomething like this has never been seen, of course, so one would assume it is very dangerous.
InProgressResponse: If you can get me the eye of that Original Guardian, this journey won't have been a waste after all.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: You survive the Lazarus Well? After you left, I deciphered clues suggesting it was even more dangerous than I knew.\n\nBut you did it! And more importantly, the Eye! Yes, this... is quite a prize!
